What is an HTTP Method?
An HTTP Method tells the server:
"This is what I want to do."
Think of it as the purpose of your request.
Example:
Browser
    │
    ▼
"I want to READ users."

or

"I want to CREATE a student."

or

"I want to DELETE a product."
The server looks at the HTTP Method and decides what action to perform.
Real-World Analogy – Library
Imagine a library.
You can perform different actions.
Borrow a book

Return a book

Update your membership details

Replace your membership details

Cancel your membership
Each action is different.
Similarly, HTTP uses different methods for different tasks.
